      • updateAccount

        public static void updateAccount(DAO sql,
                                 <any> accountBeanList,
                                 AccountBean accountBeanWithValuesSet)
                          throws java.lang.Exception
        The method modifies the list of accounts given updating a set of attributes specified into the account given. The methods updates these attributes: 1. BLOCK CODE (Block block) 2. NUMBER OF LOGIN ERROR (Long numberLoginError) 3. LAST CHANGE PASSWORD (Date lastChangePwd) 4. LAST LOGIN (Date lastWrongLogin) 5. FORCE CHANGE PASSWORD (Boolean forceChangePwd) 6. EXPIRE DATE (Date expire)
        Parameters:
        sql - mandatory connection parameter
        accountBeanList - list of accounts to modify
        accountBeanWithValuesSet - account with the set of attributes used to update the list of accounts
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • matchAccount

        public static <any> matchAccount(DAO sql,
                                 UserBean uBean,
                                 AccountBean accountBean)
                          throws java.lang.Exception
        The method match the user given with the account given. If the account given is already matched with another user, the method first provides unmatch operation. When unmatch is called, if there are entitlements removed, these will be assigned to the user given after match operaton. Note! If necessary, the entitlements are assigned to the ou of the user in visibility violation.
        Parameters:
        sql - mandatory connection parameter
        uBean - user to match, mandatory
        accountBean - account to match, mandatory
        Returns:
        list of entitlement removed (and assigned to the user given) after unmatch operation
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • unMatchAccount

        public static <any> unMatchAccount(DAO sql,
                                   AccountBean accountBean)
                            throws java.lang.Exception
        The method unmatch the account given to the user which is associated with. The account status become ORPHAN and, if present, the entitlements are removed from the user.
        Parameters:
        sql - mandatory connection parameter
        accountBean - account filter, mandatory
        Returns:
        list of entitlements removed
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
